{"parse":{"title":"Folly fort","pageid":47861215,"revid":816923012,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>A <b>folly fort</b> or just <b>folly</b> is a specific type of fort built in shallow water, near the shore, in the second half of the 19th century.  The main characteristic of a folly fort was that it was built on the water, very close to the edge, very small, and exclusively for military defense with no intention of being used as normal living quarters.  They were really defense fortifications rather than what were called \"forts\" at the time, which were on land and much larger.\n</p><p>The name derives from forts built at the time in the south of England by <a href=\"/wiki/Henry_Temple,_3rd_Viscount_Palmerston\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Henry Temple, 3rd Viscount Palmerston\">Lord Palmerston</a> and which were called \"<a href=\"/wiki/Palmerston_Forts\" title=\"Palmerston Forts\">Palmerston's follies</a>\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Later, similar forts built by the Europeans in China came to be called \"folly fort\" or simply \"folly\".\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Dutch_folly_fort.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/69/Dutch_folly_fort.jpg/220px-Dutch_folly_fort.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"160\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/69/Dutch_folly_fort.jpg/330px-Dutch_folly_fort.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/69/Dutch_folly_fort.jpg/440px-Dutch_folly_fort.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"640\" data-file-height=\"466\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Dutch_folly_fort.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The Dutch folly, located in <a href=\"/wiki/Guangzhou\" title=\"Guangzhou\">Canton</a></div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>French Folly</b> and <b>Dutch Folly</b> were forts in the <a href=\"/wiki/Pearl_River_(China)\" title=\"Pearl River (China)\">Pearl River</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Guangzhou\" title=\"Guangzhou\">Guangzhou</a> (then <a href=\"/wiki/Romanization_of_Chinese\" title=\"Romanization of Chinese\">romanized</a> as \"Canton\"), which the Europeans used during the <a href=\"/wiki/Second_Opium_War\" title=\"Second Opium War\">Second Opium War</a>.\n</p><p>The Dutch folly was located at <span class=\"plainlinks nourlexpansion\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//tools.wmflabs.org/geohack/geohack.php?pagename=Folly_fort&amp;params=23.1134_N_113.2551_E_type:landmark_region:CN\"><span class=\"geo-nondefault\"><span class=\"geo-dms\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\"><span class=\"latitude\">23\u00b006\u203248\u2033N</span> <span class=\"longitude\">113\u00b015\u203218\u2033E</span></span></span><span class=\"geo-multi-punct\">&#xfeff; / &#xfeff;</span><span class=\"geo-default\"><span class=\"geo-dec\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\">23.1134\u00b0N 113.2551\u00b0E</span><span style=\"display:none\">&#xfeff; / <span class=\"geo\">23.1134; 113.2551</span></span></span></a></span>, which was then a small island in the river. Today two skyscrapers stand in the same place, which is at the water's edge and no longer an island due to land reclamation.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tleft\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:A_battle_at_French_Folly_Fort.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/20/A_battle_at_French_Folly_Fort.jpg/220px-A_battle_at_French_Folly_Fort.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"169\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/20/A_battle_at_French_Folly_Fort.jpg/330px-A_battle_at_French_Folly_Fort.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/20/A_battle_at_French_Folly_Fort.jpg/440px-A_battle_at_French_Folly_Fort.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"611\" data-file-height=\"470\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:A_battle_at_French_Folly_Fort.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><i>A battle at French Folly Fort</i> by a Chinese painter</div></div></div>\n<p>The French folly was located at <span class=\"plainlinks nourlexpansion\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//tools.wmflabs.org/geohack/geohack.php?pagename=Folly_fort&amp;params=23.1205_N_113.2772_E_type:landmark_region:CN\"><span class=\"geo-nondefault\"><span class=\"geo-dms\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\"><span class=\"latitude\">23\u00b007\u203214\u2033N</span> <span class=\"longitude\">113\u00b016\u203238\u2033E</span></span></span><span class=\"geo-multi-punct\">&#xfeff; / &#xfeff;</span><span class=\"geo-default\"><span class=\"geo-dec\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\">23.1205\u00b0N 113.2772\u00b0E</span><span style=\"display:none\">&#xfeff; / <span class=\"geo\">23.1205; 113.2772</span></span></span></a></span>, which is now well inland due to land reclamation. The British <a href=\"/wiki/Capture_of_the_French_Folly_Fort\" title=\"Capture of the French Folly Fort\">captured it</a> on 6 November 1856 in an intense, one-hour action during the <a href=\"/wiki/Second_Opium_War\" title=\"Second Opium War\">second Opium War</a>.\n</p><p>A similar fort that saw action at the time was Macao Fort (<span class=\"plainlinks nourlexpansion\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//tools.wmflabs.org/geohack/geohack.php?pagename=Folly_fort&amp;params=23.0728_N_113.2527_E_type:landmark_region:CN\"><span class=\"geo-nondefault\"><span class=\"geo-dms\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\"><span class=\"latitude\">23\u00b004\u203222\u2033N</span> <span class=\"longitude\">113\u00b015\u203210\u2033E</span></span></span><span class=\"geo-multi-punct\">&#xfeff; / &#xfeff;</span><span class=\"geo-default\"><span class=\"geo-dec\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\">23.0728\u00b0N 113.2527\u00b0E</span><span style=\"display:none\">&#xfeff; / <span class=\"geo\">23.0728; 113.2527</span></span></span></a></span>), but it was never called \"folly\", possibly because the Chinese built it on a larger island that also had a temple. This island, fort, and temple still exist.\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Canton1860.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/da/Canton1860.jpg/220px-Canton1860.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"126\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/da/Canton1860.jpg/330px-Canton1860.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/da/Canton1860.jpg/440px-Canton1860.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"11680\" data-file-height=\"6672\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Canton1860.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>1860 map of Canton showing the folly forts</div></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Folly_fort&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.classicboat.co.uk/news/palmerstons-follies-saved-for-the-nation/\">http://www.classicboat.co.uk/news/palmerstons-follies-saved-for-the-nation/</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">See <a class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:Dutch_Folly_Fort\">[1]</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Column_impost.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/Column_impost.svg/34px-Column_impost.svg.png\" width=\"34\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/Column_impost.svg/51px-Column_impost.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/Column_impost.svg/68px-Column_impost.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"140\" data-file-height=\"123\" /></a></td><td><i>This <a href=\"/wiki/Architecture\" title=\"Architecture\">architecture</a>-related article is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Folly_fort&amp;action=edit\">expanding it</a>.</i><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\" style=\"position: absolute; right: 15px; display: none;\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Architecture-stub\" title=\"Template:Architecture-stub\"><abbr title=\"View this template\">v</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template_talk:Architecture-stub\" title=\"Template talk:Architecture-stub\"><abbr title=\"Discuss this template\">t</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-edit\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Architecture-stub&amp;action=edit\"><abbr title=\"Edit this template\">e</abbr></a></li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"back